  "notes": "Livvi-Karelian (livvinkarjala / Olonets Karelian), Republic of Karelia (Russia). Written in the Latin-based Karelian alphabet (2007 unified norm; <ü> was replaced by <y>). Values follow the Finnic convention: <a>=/ɑ/, <ä>=/æ/, <ö>=/ø/, <y>=/y/, <c>=/ts/, <č>=/tʃ/, <š>=/ʃ/, <ž>=/ʒ/, <v>=/ʋ/. Vowel and consonant length are written with doubled letters (compositional, not listed as separate graphemes). Palatalisation of dentals before front vowels is allophonic and not written.",
